$values.Name: ErrorLog
$values.Comment: Audit table tracking errors in the the AdventureWorks database that are caught by the CATCH block of a TRY...CATCH construct. Data is inserted by stored procedure dbo.uspLogError when it is executed from inside the CATCH block of a TRY...CATCH construct.

$values.Name: ErrorLogID
$values.Comment: Primary key for ErrorLog records.

$values.Name: ErrorTime
$values.Comment: The date and time at which the error occurred.

$values.Name: UserName
$values.Comment: The user who executed the batch in which the error occurred.

$values.Name: ErrorNumber
$values.Comment: The error number of the error that occurred.

$values.Name: ErrorSeverity
$values.Comment: The severity of the error that occurred.

$values.Name: ErrorState
$values.Comment: The state number of the error that occurred.

$values.Name: ErrorProcedure
$values.Comment: The name of the stored procedure or trigger where the error occurred.

$values.Name: ErrorLine
$values.Comment: The line number at which the error occurred.

$values.Name: ErrorMessage
$values.Comment: The message text of the error that occurred.
